##The truth about a plane ticket: ONLINE TRAVEL PLATFORM BECOMES A scapegoat?

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Our reporter, Li Tian, reporting from Beijing

"We actually have a big problem right now, that is, everyone says we have a slow and difficult refund, as if everyone thinks we have eaten the money, " he said on March 12, zhang Jin, an Ota online travel entrepreneur, told China business daily under an assumed name.

In 2020, the outbreak and control of NCP brought an unprecedented demand for the Ota Platform. Mainstream Ota Platform side introduced a number of retrogression policy, even up to 1 billion yuan level. Despite the pressure on money, there are still a lot of complaints from users.

According to the reporter's investigation, in fact, a ticket back to change, involved in the online platform side, agents, airlines and other stakeholders. Among them, the platform side of the right to speak is one of the smaller, trust-building part of the enterprise "headache. ".

On March 13, Lin Zhijie, a civil aviation practitioner, told reporters that the main difficulties brought about by the epidemic to the civil aviation industry were: First, the number of refunds increased sharply, and the service capacity could not keep pace with it. A total of 20 million tickets were refunded by civil aviation, with refunds exceeding 20 billion yuan. Just two weeks more than the last five years or so combined. Airline customer service simply can not receive so many calls, and some airlines have not been able to complete the system's function of "automatic refund of epidemic situation" within a few days. Second, agents and platforms "have no money to be refunded, " agents and platforms help passengers refund their tickets, and advance money first, it may take a few days to receive a refund from the airline, so large-scale refund, some agents and platforms can not sell tickets, hands not so much money, will also lead to "no money to refund. ".

The financial pressure of free refunds

This year by the new crown pneumonia epidemic, a large number of passenger itinerary changes, the demand for refund of air tickets surge. January 23, the Civil Aviation Authority issued a notice, January 24, has bought a civil aviation ticket passengers can refund free of charge.

It is reported that during the epidemic, the flying pig back into the peak value of daily calls to more than 10 times. "A lot of tickets are already in the refund process, but the process is slow to coordinate with the airlines, which makes consumers wait longer, " Fei Zhu public relations staff told reporters.

Go where net public relations personage says to the reporter, Air Ticket refunds flow is: The user initiates refunds, airline examines and refunds to the platform, refunds to the user by the platform. The original airline refund cycle is generally 7 working days, a special type of Refund Audit Refund cycle is 30 working days. But under the outbreak, most airlines review refund cycle for 30 to 60 days. Because the refund link involves agents, domestic and foreign airlines and other 46 decision steps, almost every order needs to be manually verified. Due to the long cycle, part of the head Ota enterprises choose to advance payment for users.

However, many users complain about the speed of refund. In the Black Cat complaints, "why do not give me a refund" similar questions, in the recent more common. And according to the reporter understanding, after the application that clicks from the user refunds a ticket, each benefit party is in fact undertaking bigger pressure.

Zhang Jin told reporters that OTA enterprises assume the role of "scapegoat. ". The current situation is that online platforms, agents, airlines have backlogs of orders. Airline cash flow is tight, return money not on time, some suspended return money. "A lot of small and medium-sized agent platforms, I don't think they will survive. "

Zhang Jin said that since the outbreak prevention and control, the Civil Aviation Administration has issued four policies, different airlines have their own standards of Implementation and Response Speed, Ota platform with the airline policy adjustment. Just sorting out the policy will take some time. Ota Platform and between the airlines, there are some agents, agents also backlogs some orders, affect communication time. In addition, before the outbreak of the epidemic, online enterprises have the interface to deal with the return order in batches, but since the epidemic prevention and control, the changing actual situation, resulting in the interface is not fully applicable, so the return order is more dependent on manual review. All three of these factors slow down order processing. In the Industry Downstream Ota enterprises in addition to their own financing of consumers, difficult to have other strong measures to consumer satisfaction.

At present, Zhang Jin's platform returned the single most is the foreign airline ticket. However, the policy requirement of the CAAC is only valid for domestic airlines. Some passengers want their overseas orders to be refunded in full, but what Ota enterprises can do is to help apply for a refund and wait for the response of Overseas Airlines. In this case, the user may have a willingness to complain. If the platform continues to advance overseas orders for change back, will increase the pressure of survival. "foreign airlines are relatively slow, and after the money comes back, they may return to the users, because if we pay for it all, there may be problems in the capital chain, " Zhang said.

Where to go, the Internet publicist specifically talked about, "In fact, the withdrawal and reform policies of different overseas airlines are also different. Some Airlines require customers to call the airline themselves to apply for a refund. Some Airlines impose restrictions on the refund, or can only return coupons to the customer's account. Some Airlines worry that they will not be able to receive calls from customers or even block calls from third-party platforms."

"There's never been a refund like this before, and it was a simple matter of a few steps. But now the policy has been changing, some airlines will not necessarily implement the standards of the Civil Aviation Authority. But if users buy tickets from us, we will definitely have the 'wok' , " Zhang Jin said.

Nevertheless, Zhang Jin mentioned that some airlines if overtime has not been refunded, the platform will consider advance payment. This involves a "sense of service" problem, because consumers will think "I don't care what the reason is, I bought the ticket here from you. " But under the wave of refunds, if all such advance, the pressure is greater.

Zou Jianjun, a professor at the China Civil Aviation Administration Cadre College, said the epidemic has had a wide impact, resulting in rapid changes, frequent rule changes and a wide range of issues. If from the OTA service attributes, there is indeed a dilemma, understood as the "Fall Guy" is not too much. "And, more importantly, the relevant policies and regulations are not decided by the Otas, all they can do is try to coordinate and communicate between customers and airlines, and even sometimes Otas can only act as message carriers in the face of the harsh policies of some airlines. Therefore, in the face of Customer Demand, the OTA is in a dilemma,"Zou said.

Zou Jianjun said that due to the wide scope and long duration of the epidemic, the difficulties faced by airlines vary from one to another. Some small airlines, or airlines already operating in difficult situations, facing the most intense "guaranteed cash flow" life and death problem, will certainly choose to extend the refund time. Even in the case of an airline that declares bankruptcy, there may be no hope of recovery.

The trust conundrum of big data

In addition to complaints due to change, consumers on Ota Platform "kill cooked" suspicion also did not eliminate.

Air Ticket "kill cooked" , generally considered to be the user of air ticket products, the price paid when the order, higher than its browsing price. Some industry insiders believe that the user's judgment, the platform's big data "kill familiar" performance, or for users in different periods of time search the same voyage information, found that the price of the last time is higher than the previous time.

Is there really such a thing as "killing an acquaintance" ? Civil Aviation Practitioners Lin Zhijie told reporters: "In the E-COMMERCE field is not to kill cooked, but in the air ticket field, at least I did not find a big data kill cooked examples. "

Where to a product manager told reporters that a ticket price by the airlines according to the season, capacity, supply and demand factors such as unified regulation. After the price is determined, the airline will enter the fare data into the airline seat management system GDS. In the domestic market, the GDS is mainly operated by Air China Travelsky, while the international market is mainly operated by Amadeus, Sabre and Travelport.

According to the reporter's understanding, CTRIP, flying pig, qunar and other third-party sales platform, must be through the GDS system, to access air fare information, and display online for users to use.

In the process, airlines will adjust their fares and other data according to market changes, and then transfer the data to the gdss. This will take time, and it will take time for travel websites to get new data from the GDSS, this creates a time lag. More importantly, the volume of global airline information data and user searches is so large that agencies such as travel websites typically pull data from the gdss once in a while, waiting for a customer to place an order, there is also a need to check the final data with the airlines through the gdss, and sometimes the time difference between the time when the user asks for the price and the time when the price is checked with the airlines through the GDS.

In other words, the price information that users see while browsing is the platform's "cache" of the latest GDS information.

Lin Zhijie is opposite because the price difference that time difference causes, hold affirmative opinion. He says he has had similar experiences.

"In fact, the same is true of the airline system. We sometimes check the tickets and see on the price calendar that there is a special ticket of 300 yuan on a certain day, but it is not actually entered, which is also the reason for the data cache. Because every time a passenger makes an inquiry, they have to scan the three-month ticket prices. The calculation is too heavy and the inquiry is very slow, so the ticket prices in the system price calendar are pre-queried and cached. Sometimes the actual ticket prices change, but the prices in the calendar are not updated,"said Lin.

Zou said the process is very short in terms of time, but in any case, there may be differences between Ota and airline instant fares, depending on the information refresh interval between airlines and Otas, and whether the refresh times are synchronized between them.

For Big Data "kill cooked" , Zou Jianjun said that the time difference caused by the price difference is one. In theory, as a good service provider, tracking customer behavior is primarily a matter of booking records, including travel times, seat requirements, and automatic screening to present consumers with an optimal recommendation, reduce Customer Search and selection time. But if the service business consumer needs to understand the wrong customer such as a public, business travel people, suddenly in Ota Search for leisure travel products, it may appear the so-called "kill cooked" problem.

Zou Jianjun believes that a mature to sales service as the main business, and rely on large network traffic, is not rashly to take such suicidal behavior. But if there is such a problem, then the Ota Platform is responsible to carry out the supervision and management.

"The board is correct in saying that it is the time difference that leads to the situation of 'the more you search, the more expensive' . In any minute and a second difference, the big warehouse The Hours Primary Colors are constantly changing, " ctrip wrote in its official Wechat Post.

Go where net platform also denied the behavior that big data kills cooked explicitly to the reporter.

According to the regulations of the Civil Aviation Administration, the platform information service management fee charged by airlines for each ticket sold can only be "paid according to the quota per ticket, " a public relations official at Qunar told reporters. This means that every ticket sold, the money the platform makes is relatively constant. There's no need for the platform to be overpriced.

The PR person said that the online travel industry is a fully competitive market and Otas have a high cost of acquiring a user. The average cost of acquiring a new user can be as high as hundreds of dollars. If you kill a user in order to earn a few more dollars, losing a user is not worthwhile at all. And once the user thinks a certain platform has the behavior that is suspected"kill cooked", they will abandon this platform very quickly. Ota Platform for small profits and lose an old user, this "not cost-effective. ". "We will finally pay before the final check to ensure the accuracy of the price, otherwise the post-payment to the existence of the price can only go to where net to bear. "

"Big data kill cooked is really no" , a former employee also told reporters that if companies want to kill cooked, to hire "hackers" to the system price, human cost pressure, also can not be ignored. According to the former employee, Ota platforms are similar to Taobao in that they sell products but do not have pricing power, and if they are self-operated like JD.com, they have some pricing power.

The former employee mentioned something. A user who bought air tickets on Qunar for many years found that there was a "change in price" and sought explanation. The Account Director and several other staff members went to the meeting to explain the matter. The employee said that the company to explain face-to-face, not only for fear of losing the user, in fact, will think the other side is their old friend, when the old friend "misunderstanding" , the company will be more difficult.

To go where net makes"kill cooked not cost-effective"explanation, Zou Jianjun thinks, speak from sale theory is such. Furthermore, as mobile smart devices become more ubiquitous and information becomes more transparent, consumer loyalty to otas continues to decline, and the cost of developing and maintaining OTAS will not increase significantly, but due to increased mobility, it also indirectly increases customer maintenance costs. In this case, the OTA does face the problem of developing new users and retaining old users.

The Reporter noticed that the OTA platform in the past few years, through the initiative to post, or even the development conference specifically to explain this matter, but why still not establish a "trust environment" ?

CTRIP's official Wechat Post suggested that one of the reasons for users' distrust might be the "separation of the vassals from the world and chaos" in the past. The size does not have the innumerable ticket distributor, the netizen "the ticket how much money after all" in the mind has no spectrum. Second, I am afraid that the Internet companies are all kinds of "work. ". Consumers think there's too much monkey business going on with Internet companies. Third: "Big Data" by many enterprises "flexible use. For example, new customers are given large coupons, which are not available to existing customers. Some carriers also offer packages for new customers, which are not available to existing customers.

According to the former employee, otas display the ticketing resources of different airlines in a centralized way, or have something to do with the role of the resources being centralized. In addition, some consumers still hold the logic of "no business without treachery" .

As for the lack of trust, Zou said there are three issues to be concerned about: First, the growth history of Otas and the so-called "poor air fare" earned by Otas in the past; and Second, the diversity of Ota Platform Services, the first two are relatively standard and easy to manage, while the second is not. The third is that there is a "blind area" of management. Strictly speaking, industry regulators have no responsibility for market management, and Airline and Ota marketing activities are managed by other relevant government functions.

As for how OTAS can improve their image and service quality, Zou suggested: First, improve the transparency of information and the timeliness of Communication; Second, strengthen platform management and strengthen the supervision and management of Third Parties; Third, focus on policy lobbying, clear Ota products and services content boundary, active docking supervision and management to accept open, transparent management.

Ticket business profit is meager, heavy in drainage

The reporter understands, with regard to the sale of air tickets and refund, there are difficult to be trusted to form a difference is that the Air Ticket Business in Ota enterprises, earning capacity is limited.

Since 2015, airlines and otas have been more sensitive to the voice of the airline business.

Lin Zhijie told reporters: "Now the policy level has been unified. ". The first two years of the air ticket agent market is quite chaotic, each agent and Ota Platform self-pricing sell, refund change the handling fee also self-determination, such as airline pricing 800 yuan, refund handling fee 20% , there are agents sell 850 yuan, there are agents sell 750 yuan, but refund handling fee 80% . Subsequently, in 2016, the Civil Aviation Administration issued a circular regulating the agency price, explicitly requiring that 'agents shall not maliciously tamper with the passenger ticket prices and applicable conditions published by the air transport enterprise in accordance with the regulations, and Bundle Sales' .

"For our platform, it's not the strong side, sometimes the strong side is 'airline Dad' , not us, " Li Hua, an OTA industry insider, told reporters under an assumed name.

"We have costs in terms of manpower, customer service, technology, we have to pay for CNAC, and there are costs in terms of SMS alerts. So, basically, our domestic air tickets are losing money, either a little or equal,"Li Hua said, the company has considered giving users stop shipping information internally to cut costs, but says users have gotten used to it.

Lin Zhijie said that in 2016, the Civil Aviation Administration issued a notice specifically requiring ticket agency fees not to be proportional, but to pay according to a fixed amount, which is how much a ticket is fixed. For example, the platform itself acts as an agent to sell a domestic first-class cabin, the agent fee is 60 yuan, sells the domestic economy cabin, the discount takes much less, the discount takes much less, approximately is 5 yuan ~ 25 yuan appearance. However, Lin Zhijie does not think that OTA is in a weak position, he mentioned, "CTRIP sells half of all airline tickets, which is quite a high share, while no domestic airline has more than a quarter of the business. "

According to our reporter, the profit of single ticket is not high, but the ticket business can be used as the source of traffic, and has value.

Qunar public relations also admitted to reporters, "generally in the tourism platform, the traffic business is the drainage business. To qunar as an example, its ticket business started, the current ticket business is the focus of the drainage business. "

"But air tickets are traffic, so you still have to do it, " Li said.

Meanwhile, Fan Lei, chief financial officer of Elong, said, "Now OTA companies, the profits of the airline sector has been very low, by 2017 the major airlines to the commission rate fell to 0.3 ~ 0.5 points, there is no room for further tightening. Especially like CTRIP, the same journey Elong Ota enterprises, more is to provide a one-stop platform, selling a ticket is only the beginning of a trip, this period to provide additional products is the main source of revenue. In 2018, we bought about 30 per cent more additional products, which is the main source of revenue for the ticket business."

"over the years, the air ticket business is really not as good as the hotel business, because now the airline booking has become white-hot, others can not make money, if you want to make money, you are more expensive than others, people will not choose you for a little comparison, " the former employee told reporters.

"The platform values the person who buys a ticket because once he buys a ticket here, he may book a hotel there, and he may buy a package tour. It's only this combination of things that can make a bit of money from this person,"the former employee said.

Zou noted that the agreements with the platform are different for each company. But for most companies, especially domestic airlines, the policy requires them to pay essentially a so-called "technical service fee. ". In fact, in theory, the revenue from Selling Air Tickets on Ota platforms is very low. Only in terms of travel service, air ticket service is the source, so everyone should expand the source of air ticket service, the source of traffic, in order to have the opportunity to provide more follow-up service for the customer.

"It's a common value logic for online businesses to maintain and expand inbound traffic, extend the service chain, and provide a wealth of follow-up products to provide customers with convenient and practical services as a basis for increasing revenue across the chain. The air ticket service is just the entrance to travel consumption, so the efforts of the platform are not difficult to understand,"Zou said.
